      "title": "Exception (الاستثناء)",
      "titleArabic": "أسلوب الاستثناء",
      "content": [
        "The exception (الاستثناء) is used to exclude something from a general statement. The main particle is إِلَّا (except).",
        "The case of the excepted noun (المستثنى) depends on the structure of the sentence."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "إِلَّا - 'except' (most common)",
        "غَيْر - 'other than' (noun, takes case of replaced word)",
        "سِوَى - 'except' (noun, always مجرور after it)",
        "In complete affirmative sentences, المستثنى is منصوب"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "جَاءَ الطُّلَّابُ إِلَّا مُحَمَّدًا", "english": "The students came except Muhammad" },
        { "arabic": "كُلُّهُمْ إِلَّا عَلِيًّا", "english": "All of them except Ali" },
        { "arabic": "مَا جَاءَ أَحَدٌ إِلَّا الْمُدَرِّسُ", "english": "No one came except the teacher" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Cases of the Excepted Noun",
      "titleArabic": "حالات المستثنى",
      "content": [
        "The case of the excepted noun varies based on sentence structure."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Complete affirmative: المستثنى is منصوب always",
        "Complete negative: Can be منصوب or follow the المستثنى منه",
        "Incomplete (no المستثنى منه): Follows grammatical role",
        "Example: مَا جَاءَ إِلَّا مُحَمَّدٌ (No one came except Muhammad - مرفوع as subject)"
      ]
    }
